The paper focuses on building vector representations of individual developers based on their coding style, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). The approach involves training a model for authorship recognition, which involves natural language processing techniques (cs.CL). The use of machine learning to build the representations also suggests relevance to machine learning (cs.LG). The representations can be used to track knowledge transfer in teams, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the representations for team structure, which could be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY).
